FBIS4-30507 "dreas124_n_94002" FBIS-EAS-94-124 Daily Report 28 Jun 1994 Vietnam Japan To Help Finance New Power Project Japan To Help Finance New Power Project BK2806102794 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 0500 GMT 28 Jun 94 BK2806102794 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network Vietnamese BFN [Text] With the aim of supplying more electric power to production establishments and people's households in the southern provinces, the prime minister recently approved a project to build the Ham Thuan-Dani Hydroelectric Power Plant. The plant will be build in areas of Tanh Linh and Ham Thuan Bac Districts in Binh Thuan Province and Bao Loc District in Lam Dong Province. Total capital for the project is more than 70 billion Japanese yen; 85 percent will come from Japanese Government ODA [overseas development aid] and 15 percent from loans sought by the Ministry of Energy. Construction will commence in early 1996.
